    "chemicalDescription": [
      "Bis-HPMA Poly(1,4-Butanediol-14/Neopentyl Glycol)/IPDI Copolymer is a urethane polymer formed by a multi-step process. First, a polyester is made by condensing Poly(1,4-Butanediol)-14 and Neopentyl Glycol, which is subsequently reacted with Isophorone Diisocyanate. The resulting polymer is end-capped with Hydroxypropyl Methacrylate"
